'''Hyarmendacil''' means "South-victor" in [[Quenya]] (from ''[[Hyarmen]]'', "South" and ''[[dacil]]'', "victor"), and can refer to:
* [[Hyarmendacil I]] ({{TA|899}} - {{TA|1149|n}}), born Ciryaher, the fifteenth [[Kings of Gondor|King]] of [[Gondor]] who ruled during the height of [[Gondor]]'s power.
* [[Hyarmendacil II]] ({{TA|1391}} - {{TA|1621|n}}), born Vinyarion, the twenty-fourth [[Kings of Gondor|King]] of [[Gondor]] who defeated a [[Haradrim]] invasion.
